    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "The cursor column facilitates _vertical movement_ & _alignment_, so it's normal behavior for it to represent the absolute column the cursor is in.\r\nHowever, it may also be used for another reasons, such as _locating_ easily the cursor on the terminal window (my case).\r\n\r\n### The problem \r\nWhen using the concealer feature of vim, the cursor column gets misaligned with the cursor, causing a very unstylish effect.\r\n\r\n### Expected behavior\r\n\r\nAdding a configuration option for the cursor column to be always aligned vertically with the cursor virtual position, rather than the absolute column the cursor is in. ",
